---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Darshnik Swamy" description="Who I am and why I write.">
  <article class="max-w-[960px] mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-text)] dark:text-[var(--color-dark-text)] mb-8">
      About
    </h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Hey, I'm Darshnik Swamy. I'm a software engineer who's endlessly curious about the patterns that connect seemingly different fields — from cricket strategy to distributed systems, from ancient history to the future of technology.
      </p>
      <p>
        By day, I work on building things with code. I've spent time thinking about data infrastructure, privacy systems, and how to make complex technical systems work at scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work, I'm probably watching cricket, exploring a new city, finding good food, or reading about some obscure historical event that changed everything.
      </p>
      <h2>Why this blog?</h2>
      <p>
        I started writing here because I realized some of the most interesting ideas I come across don't fit neatly into a tweet or a LinkedIn post. They need space — space to explore, to draw connections, to tell stories.
      </p>
      <p>
        This blog is where I do that. I write about sport, history, tech, and the future — and the surprising ways they connect. Expect long-form essays, the occasional diagram, and hopefully a few ideas that make you see something differently.
      </p>
      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        You can find me on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/darshnik-swamy/">LinkedIn</a> or <a href="https://github.com/Darshnik">GitHub</a>. I'd love to hear from you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
